Below, the education variables from the ACS survey are aggregated into a city human capital index (CHCI) using a basic function.
```{r chci_variable}
chciindex <- function(data_frame) {       #takes a data_frame as input, returns newly calc variable
  chci <- ((50* data_frame$ed_below9e + 100*data_frame$ed_hsnodip_e + # assigning new variable chci  
            120*data_frame$ed_hsdip_e + 130* data_frame$ed_scollege_e + 
            140* data_frame$ed_associate_e + 190*data_frame$ed_bachelor_e + #must specify to look into a df, find these vars
              230*data_frame$graddeg_higher_e))/ 100    # named variables, hence 'df$variable name'
  return(chci)
}
```

