```{r outliers_function, echo = FALSE, warning = FALSE, message = FALSE}
rm_outliers_col <- function(column, multiplier = 8) {
  Q1 <- quantile(column, 0.25, na.rm = TRUE)
  Q3 <- quantile(column, 0.75, na.rm = TRUE)
  IQR <- Q3 - Q1
  lower_bound <- Q1 - multiplier * IQR
  upper_bound <- Q3 + multiplier * IQR
  column >= lower_bound & column <= upper_bound
}

remove_outliers_df <- function(df, multiplier = 8) {
  # Apply the outlier removal function to each numeric column
  is_outlier <- df %>%
    select(where(is.numeric)) %>%
    mutate(across(everything(), ~ rm_outliers_col(.,multiplier))) %>%
    rowSums() == ncol(select(df, where(is.numeric)))
  
  df[is_outlier, ]
}
```

To properly visualize relationships among variables of interest, outliers are removed using a straightforward IQR upper and lower bound method. Approximately 700 observations are removed from the original 3139 observations. 

